    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Some posts make readers want to leave <em>really</em> long comments that would really be better suited as their own blog posts.</p>\n<p>This itty bitty plugin will give your rambling commenters a hint.</p>\n<p>Inspired by <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jenmylo\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Jen Mylo&#8217;s</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/jenmylo/status/111586232231931905\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">tweet</a></p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Unzip &#8216;comment-overload.zip&#8217; and upload to your plugin directory (default: wp-content/plugins/).</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;plugins&#8217; page in WP.</li>\n<li>Customize in Settings &gt; Discussion</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<h4>none yet</h4>\n<p></p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>Version 1.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>maintenance</li>\n<li>verify compat with WP 4.6</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>translatable</li>\n<li>reworked to simplify js and php code</li>\n<li>option for subtler inline alerts after the first.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>enqueue scripts correctly</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Now with customizable options!</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
    "short_description": "Alert commenters when they begin writing too many paragraphs.",
